line_1: Wit grates the Ear, and melting Musick tires:
line_2: Gay Robes no more the aking Sight admires,

line_1: The curious eye their awkward movement tires;
line_2: They seem like puppets led about by wires.

line_1: Whose wit is rudeness, whose good breeding tires;
line_2: He chuses company, but not the squire's,

line_1: Pursues in vain; where youth itself soon tires,
line_2: Spite of the transports that the chace inspires;

line_1: My Ear no more your sprightly Musick tires:
line_2: Come here (she cry'd) ye soft aërial Choirs;

line_1: And what Bootes' lazy wagon tires;
line_2: Whence the Seven Sisters' congregated fires,
